{
  "texts": [
    "In 1906, Dr. Alois Alzheimer was the first to discover AD [37,63].",
    "It is typified by a progressive loss of memory and other cognitive abilities [70].",
    "With 70% of dementia cases, AD is the most prevalent type of dementia worldwide.",
    "AD is a cognitive disorder affecting cognitive function and memory, and is a leading cause of dementia in elderly individuals [48].",
    "Over time, there is an irreversible decline in cognitive function associated with this progressive neurological disorder."
  ]
}